00:23:40,852 --> 00:23:42,183
Ned!

284
00:23:42,253 --> 00:23:43,345
[Twigs Crunch]

285
00:23:43,421 --> 00:23:44,513
Get out of here!

286
00:23:44,589 --> 00:23:45,681
Ned!

287
00:23:45,757 --> 00:23:46,849
Aah!

288
00:23:46,925 --> 00:23:48,859
[Ned]
I'm getting to you.

289
00:23:48,927 --> 00:23:50,019
Very slowly.

290
00:23:50,094 --> 00:23:51,823
Ha ha! You!

291
00:23:51,896 --> 00:23:53,329
Hey, you guys.

292
00:23:53,398 --> 00:23:56,333
You ready to go back to work?

293
00:23:56,401 --> 00:23:57,868
Yeah.

294
00:23:57,936 --> 00:23:59,028
Ohh.

295
00:23:59,103 --> 00:24:00,297
Come on, Alice.

296
00:24:00,371 --> 00:24:01,633
Help!

297
00:24:01,706 --> 00:24:04,800
Help! Help!

298
00:24:04,876 --> 00:24:06,138
Something's wrong with Ned.

299
00:24:07,312 --> 00:24:09,371
Get a life preserver!

300
00:24:26,564 --> 00:24:27,997
Is it far?
Can he swim?

301
00:24:28,066 --> 00:24:30,694
He's right around here somewhere.

302
00:24:32,036 --> 00:24:33,970
Go ahead.
Dive for him.

303
00:24:36,341 --> 00:24:37,774
There he is.

304
00:24:37,842 --> 00:24:39,275
Come on, you guys.
Help us.

305
00:24:39,344 --> 00:24:40,777
Watch his head.

306
00:24:40,845 --> 00:24:42,278
Here.
Grab hold of that.

307
00:24:42,347 --> 00:24:43,439
O.K.

308
00:24:43,514 --> 00:24:44,947
Move it away.

309
00:24:45,016 --> 00:24:47,109
Watch his head.

310
00:24:47,185 --> 00:24:48,277
Got him?

311
00:24:48,353 --> 00:24:49,445
Yeah.

312
00:24:51,623 --> 00:24:52,715
[Coughing]

313
00:24:55,360 --> 00:24:57,794
Do you give mouth-to-mouth?

314
00:24:57,862 --> 00:24:59,796
Yeah.
Pull up his head.

315
00:25:03,801 --> 00:25:04,893
Oh, God.

316
00:25:04,969 --> 00:25:06,436
Come on, Neddie.

317
00:25:06,504 --> 00:25:07,402
Come on.

318
00:25:07,472 --> 00:25:08,734
Oh, Neddie!

319
00:25:08,806 --> 00:25:10,603
Oh, Jesus Christ!

320
00:25:46,744 --> 00:25:47,836
Aah!

321
00:25:53,351 --> 00:25:55,080
Bill!

322
00:25:55,153 --> 00:25:56,279
Bill!

323
00:25:56,354 --> 00:25:57,787
Come here quick!

324
00:25:57,855 --> 00:25:59,015
Hurry!

325
00:26:03,327 --> 00:26:04,692
What is it?

326
00:26:04,762 --> 00:26:07,230
There's a snake over there.

327
00:26:07,298 --> 00:26:08,390
Where?

328
00:26:15,807 --> 00:26:17,240
What do l do?

329
00:26:17,308 --> 00:26:18,400
Kill it.

330
00:26:18,476 --> 00:26:19,909
It might bite.

331
00:26:19,977 --> 00:26:22,411
Haven't you ever been in the woods?

332
00:26:22,480 --> 00:26:23,913
We're not in the woods.

333
00:26:23,981 --> 00:26:25,915
Jesus, Bill, what are you doing?

334
00:26:25,983 --> 00:26:27,416
There's a snake in here.

335
00:26:27,485 --> 00:26:29,419
Then why are we in here?

336
00:26:29,487 --> 00:26:30,920
Feet, don't fail me now.

337
00:26:30,988 --> 00:26:32,353
There it is!
Ahh!

338
00:26:32,423 --> 00:26:35,358
l can't sleep with a snake in here.

339
00:26:35,426 --> 00:26:37,360
Nobody told us anything
about snakes.

340
00:26:37,428 --> 00:26:38,520
Kill it.

341
00:26:38,596 --> 00:26:40,029
You heard the lady.

342
00:26:40,098 --> 00:26:43,033
l can't get it till it comes out.

343
00:26:43,101 --> 00:26:44,033
Call him.

344
00:26:44,102 --> 00:26:46,036
How do you call a snake?

345
00:26:46,104 --> 00:26:47,537
I'll flush it out!

346
00:26:47,605 --> 00:26:48,970
No!

347
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:50,337
- Aah!
- Aah!

348
00:26:52,543 --> 00:26:53,976
l got it!

349
00:26:54,045 --> 00:26:55,137
Where?

350
00:26:55,213 --> 00:26:57,545
l got it!

351
00:26:57,615 --> 00:26:59,139
Kill it!

352
00:27:07,125 --> 00:27:08,558
Is it dead?

353
00:27:08,626 --> 00:27:12,062
Either that or it's got
a very short clone.

354
00:27:12,130 --> 00:27:13,722
Oh, God.

355
00:27:13,798 --> 00:27:17,234
Well, at least we know
what's for dinner.

356
00:27:17,301 --> 00:27:19,360
- Oh!
- Oh, Marcie!
- Gross!

357
00:27:23,274 --> 00:27:24,707
l make good salad.

358
00:27:24,776 --> 00:27:26,710
Want me to make bread pudding?

359
00:27:26,778 --> 00:27:27,904
Great.
We've got hamburger.

360
00:27:27,979 --> 00:27:29,412
None for me, thank you.

361
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:32,415
There are apples.
Know how to make apple pie?

362
00:27:32,483 --> 00:27:33,916
Oh, sure.
No sweat.

363
00:27:33,985 --> 00:27:35,919
Oh, what is going on?

364
00:27:35,987 --> 00:27:37,818
[Whooping]

365
00:27:37,889 --> 00:27:40,983
[Whooping]

366
00:27:46,164 --> 00:27:47,392
Oh, shit.

367
00:27:49,433 --> 00:27:51,867
All right, who are you people?

368
00:27:51,936 --> 00:27:53,028
Camp counselors.

369
00:27:53,104 --> 00:27:54,537
Neddie's just fooling around.

370
00:27:54,605 --> 00:27:56,038
Right, I'm just--

371
00:27:56,107 --> 00:27:57,540
Can it, Cochise.

372
00:27:57,608 --> 00:27:59,041
Steve Christy hire you people?

373
00:27:59,110 --> 00:28:00,543
He pay you for this?

374
00:28:00,611 --> 00:28:01,703
Nice bike.

375
00:28:01,779 --> 00:28:03,212
See if you're smoking, boy.

376
00:28:03,281 --> 00:28:04,646
Don't smoke.
Causes cancer.

377
00:28:04,715 --> 00:28:06,649
You just get off a spaceship?

378
00:28:06,717 --> 00:28:09,652
Colombian gold, man, grass,
hash, the weed. Dig it?

379
00:28:09,720 --> 00:28:11,153
Hey, what's he talking about?

380
00:28:11,222 --> 00:28:12,655
Hey, don't get smart.

381
00:28:12,723 --> 00:28:14,657
Me? I'm dumb as they come.

382
00:28:14,725 --> 00:28:17,626
Not another word
out of you, understand?

383
00:28:17,695 --> 00:28:19,128
Really.
Nothing's going on here.

384
00:28:19,197 --> 00:28:21,131
We're getting the place in shape.

385
00:28:21,199 --> 00:28:22,632
In shape for what?

386
00:28:22,700 --> 00:28:24,224
Officer, can we help?

387
00:28:24,302 --> 00:28:25,735
Looking for somebody.

388
00:28:25,803 --> 00:28:26,895
Who's that?

389
00:28:26,971 --> 00:28:29,405
A guy named Ralph.
Town crazy.

390
00:28:29,473 --> 00:28:30,906
No crazy people around here.

391
00:28:30,975 --> 00:28:33,910
l told you to sit on it, Tonto.

392
00:28:33,978 --> 00:28:37,914
l got word that Ralph
was pedaling out this way

393
00:28:37,982 --> 00:28:39,506
spouting his gospel.

394
00:28:39,584 --> 00:28:41,518
We haven't seen anybody here,
Officer.

395
00:28:41,586 --> 00:28:42,678
Just us.

396
00:28:42,753 --> 00:28:44,482
This Ralph, is he dangerous?

397
00:28:44,555 --> 00:28:46,489
Every time that loony gets drunk,

398
00:28:46,557 --> 00:28:47,990
he gets his calling.

399
00:28:48,059 --> 00:28:50,493
l spend the morning in court,

400
00:28:50,561 --> 00:28:52,495
he gets a week in jail.

401
00:28:52,563 --> 00:28:53,996
Cycle Two, where are you?

402
00:28:54,065 --> 00:28:55,362
Come in, Cycle Two.

403
00:28:55,433 --> 00:28:57,867
This is Dorf at Camp Crystal Lake.
Over.

404
00:28:57,935 --> 00:28:59,368
Haul it back in.

405
00:28:59,437 --> 00:29:02,372
Chief wants you back on the double.

406
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:05,603
Roger that. 10-4.
On my way. Out.

407
00:29:07,278 --> 00:29:09,644
Never keep the chief waiting.

408
00:29:12,283 --> 00:29:14,717
You kids keep your noses clean.
Understand?

409
00:29:14,785 --> 00:29:17,413
You'll be hearing
from me if you don't.

410
00:29:20,291 --> 00:29:24,318
We ain't going to stand
for no weirdness out here.

411
00:30:05,569 --> 00:30:06,661
Aah!

412
00:30:08,239 --> 00:30:10,764
I'm the messenger of God.

413
00:30:10,841 --> 00:30:14,971
You're doomed if you stay here.

414
00:30:17,148 --> 00:30:18,581
This place is cursed.

415
00:30:18,649 --> 00:30:20,810
Cursed.

416
00:30:22,353 --> 00:30:24,287
It's got a death curse.

417
00:30:24,355 --> 00:30:25,788
Who are you?

418
00:30:25,856 --> 00:30:27,289
What do you want?

419
00:30:27,358 --> 00:30:29,292
God sent me.

420
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:31,294
Get out of here, man.

421
00:30:31,362 --> 00:30:33,296
l got to warn you.

422
00:30:33,364 --> 00:30:36,527
You're doomed if you stay.

423
00:30:37,868 --> 00:30:40,063
Go.

424
00:30:40,137 --> 00:30:41,502
Go!

425
00:30:52,516 --> 00:30:54,950
l think we just met Ralph.

426
00:30:55,019 --> 00:30:56,987
God, what's next?

427
00:31:07,664 --> 00:31:09,256
You're doomed.

428
00:31:09,332 --> 00:31:11,766
You're all doomed.

429
00:31:37,594 --> 00:31:39,027
Who likes them rare?

430
00:31:39,095 --> 00:31:40,187
Me.

431
00:31:40,263 --> 00:31:42,697
How can you guys eat that stuff?

432
00:31:42,766 --> 00:31:44,199
It looks like dead animals.

433
00:31:44,267 --> 00:31:46,167
Dead animals?
That's the old counselors.

434
00:31:46,236 --> 00:31:47,430
You cannibal.

435
00:31:47,504 --> 00:31:50,371
lf you'd mix right,
you'd get all your protein.

436
00:31:50,440 --> 00:31:52,374
Too bad Annie never showed up.

437
00:31:52,442 --> 00:31:54,876
She was supposed to be a good cook.

438
00:31:54,945 --> 00:31:56,776
Don't expect me to replace her.

439
00:31:56,846 --> 00:31:57,938
Trouble?

440
00:31:58,014 --> 00:31:59,948
Bad bulb or no power.

441
00:32:00,016 --> 00:32:02,450
It seems a little gloomy in here.

442
00:32:02,519 --> 00:32:05,386
Steve taught me how to use
the emergency generator.

443
00:32:05,455 --> 00:32:07,389
Town power lines are real lousy.

444
00:32:07,457 --> 00:32:10,392
Don't you love that macho talk?

445
00:32:10,460 --> 00:32:12,587
The emergency generator.

446
00:32:12,662 --> 00:32:13,754
Let's go.

447
00:32:13,830 --> 00:32:15,764
I'll take care of these.

448
00:32:15,832 --> 00:32:17,766
Will you watch the burgers?

449
00:32:17,834 --> 00:32:18,926
Burn them.

450
00:32:19,002 --> 00:32:20,094
Want cheese?

451
00:32:20,170 --> 00:32:21,296
Yeah, uh-huh.

452
00:32:21,371 --> 00:32:24,306
You really think
you can get this to work?

453
00:32:24,374 --> 00:32:25,807
l don't know.

454
00:32:25,875 --> 00:32:27,809
Hey, this looks like the one

455
00:32:27,877 --> 00:32:30,311
at my uncle's cabin in Maine.

456
00:32:30,380 --> 00:32:31,813
Well, here goes.

457
00:32:31,881 --> 00:32:33,314
What an antique.

458
00:32:33,383 --> 00:32:34,475
O.K.

459
00:32:34,551 --> 00:32:35,643
[Cranking]

460
00:32:35,719 --> 00:32:37,152
[Motor Starts]

461
00:32:42,359 --> 00:32:44,793
What hath God wrought?

462
00:33:44,521 --> 00:33:46,853
[Whistling]

463
00:33:58,268 --> 00:33:59,758
[Creak]

464
00:34:02,439 --> 00:34:03,633
Hello?

465
00:34:13,316 --> 00:34:15,079
Can l help you?

466
00:34:22,158 --> 00:34:23,250
Hello?

467
00:34:24,327 --> 00:34:25,555
Hello?

468
00:34:26,996 --> 00:34:28,088
Come on.

469
00:34:28,164 --> 00:34:29,597
I'm coming.
I'm coming.

470
00:34:31,334 --> 00:34:32,426
Man.

471
00:34:32,502 --> 00:34:33,935
Ooh, wind's come up.

472
00:34:34,003 --> 00:34:36,437
It shifted a good 180 degrees.

473
00:34:36,506 --> 00:34:40,670
Need someone to hold on to.

474
00:34:44,180 --> 00:34:45,613
What about Ned?

475
00:34:45,682 --> 00:34:47,115
l don't love Ned.

476
00:34:47,183 --> 00:34:50,118
He keeps acting like such a jerk.

477
00:34:50,186 --> 00:34:51,278
Neddie!

478
00:34:51,354 --> 00:34:52,787
Don't call him.

479
00:34:52,856 --> 00:34:55,290
l thought you wanted to give him

480
00:34:55,358 --> 00:34:57,292
one of your motherly lectures.

481
00:34:57,360 --> 00:35:00,295
Neddie's going to do
whatever Neddie wants to.

482
00:35:00,363 --> 00:35:02,297
Ooh, it's going to storm.

483
00:35:02,365 --> 00:35:06,233
It'll tear down that valley
like a son of a gun.

484
00:35:06,302 --> 00:35:09,066
I've feared storms
since l was little.

485
00:35:09,139 --> 00:35:10,299
No. Really?

486
00:35:10,373 --> 00:35:14,241
Yeah. I've had this dream
about five or six times

487
00:35:14,310 --> 00:35:16,244
where I'm in a thunderstorm--

488
00:35:16,312 --> 00:35:17,404
Mm-hmm.

489
00:35:17,480 --> 00:35:19,448
and it's raining really hard.

490
00:35:19,516 --> 00:35:22,952
It sounds like pebbles
when it hits the ground.

491
00:35:23,019 --> 00:35:24,452
l can hear it.

492
00:35:24,521 --> 00:35:28,457
l try to block out
the sound with my hands,

493
00:35:28,525 --> 00:35:29,958
only it doesn't work.

494
00:35:30,026 --> 00:35:33,257
It just keeps getting
louder and louder.

495
00:35:33,329 --> 00:35:34,626
And then...

496
00:35:35,832 --> 00:35:38,266
the rain turns to blood.

497
00:35:39,402 --> 00:35:43,304
The blood washes away
in little rivers.

498
00:35:44,841 --> 00:35:47,742
Then the sound stops.

499
00:35:50,346 --> 00:35:51,779
It's just a dream.

500
00:35:51,848 --> 00:35:53,281
Yeah, l know.

501
00:35:53,349 --> 00:35:55,783
l call it my shower dream.

502
00:35:55,852 --> 00:35:58,286
Hey, hey, this is no dream.

503
00:35:58,354 --> 00:36:01,380
Come on.
We're going to get soaked.

504
00:37:55,838 --> 00:37:57,271
[Thunder]

505
00:37:59,008 --> 00:38:00,441
[Playing Classical Guitar]

506
00:38:00,510 --> 00:38:03,377
Jack and Marcie are
going to get drenched.

507
00:38:03,446 --> 00:38:06,472
Not if they're where
l think they are.

508
00:38:32,642 --> 00:38:33,734
That's nice.

509
00:38:33,810 --> 00:38:34,902
Mm-hmm.

510
00:38:34,978 --> 00:38:36,070
Hey...

511
00:38:36,145 --> 00:38:38,079
l know what we can do.

512
00:38:38,147 --> 00:38:39,580
We're going to play Monopoly.

513
00:38:39,649 --> 00:38:41,082
l hate Monopoly.

514
00:38:41,150 --> 00:38:43,175
Not the way l play it.

515
00:38:43,252 --> 00:38:46,483
We're going to play strip Monopoly.

516
00:38:46,556 --> 00:38:48,490
You have got to be kidding.

517
00:38:48,558 --> 00:38:50,492
What about if Steve walks in?

518
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:51,993
We'll give him a handicap.

519
00:38:52,061 --> 00:38:53,995
He can keep his boots on.

520
00:38:54,063 --> 00:38:55,496
Everything else goes.

521
00:38:55,565 --> 00:38:56,998
Instead of paying rent,

522
00:38:57,066 --> 00:38:58,499
you pay clothes.

523
00:38:58,568 --> 00:39:00,001
Bill can be banker,

524
00:39:00,069 --> 00:39:01,866
unless, of course, he's chicken.

525
00:39:01,938 --> 00:39:05,305
Heaven help you if you land
on one of my hotels.

526
00:39:05,375 --> 00:39:07,502
See if Marcie left any grass.

527
00:39:07,577 --> 00:39:09,511
What happened to my 500?

528
00:39:09,579 --> 00:39:12,707
Right there.
Where's my shoe?

529
00:40:20,750 --> 00:40:23,685
I'm not going to pass go
without a glow.

530
00:40:23,753 --> 00:40:25,687
We already rolled for you.

531
00:40:25,755 --> 00:40:27,188
You're going last.

532
00:40:27,256 --> 00:40:28,689
Oh, and Community Chest

533
00:40:28,758 --> 00:40:31,192
cannot give you your clothes back.

534
00:40:32,361 --> 00:40:33,453
Double sixes.

535
00:40:33,529 --> 00:40:34,962
l get to roll again.

536
00:40:35,031 --> 00:40:36,965
l think we're being hustled.

537
00:40:37,033 --> 00:40:39,024
l think you're right.

538
00:40:42,371 --> 00:40:45,306
You are so fine.

539
00:40:52,381 --> 00:40:54,315
Where you going?

540
00:40:54,383 --> 00:40:56,647
l got to pee.

541
00:41:01,390 --> 00:41:03,756
Hurry back, O.K.?

542
00:41:03,826 --> 00:41:05,760
It's getting cold in here.

543
00:41:14,837 --> 00:41:16,771
Save my place for me.

544
00:41:16,839 --> 00:41:17,931
Oh, yeah.

545
00:41:36,526 --> 00:41:37,618
Five.

546
00:41:37,693 --> 00:41:40,628
1, 2, 3, 4, 5.
''Baltic Avenue.''

547
00:41:40,696 --> 00:41:42,129
I'll buy it.

548
00:41:42,198 --> 00:41:44,632
No one ever lands
on Baltic Avenue.

549
00:41:44,700 --> 00:41:46,133
It's a pretty color.

550
00:41:46,202 --> 00:41:47,294
O.K.

551
00:41:47,370 --> 00:41:48,803
Come on.

552
00:41:48,871 --> 00:41:49,963
Ha! Eight!

553
00:41:50,039 --> 00:41:52,974
1, 2, doo doo doo
doo doo doo.

554
00:41:53,042 --> 00:41:55,306
Baltic Avenue.

555
00:41:55,378 --> 00:41:57,312
You owe me one boot.

556
00:41:57,380 --> 00:41:58,472
Coming.

557
00:41:58,548 --> 00:41:59,981
Alice draws first blood.

558
00:42:00,049 --> 00:42:03,416
That's a terrible way
to talk about my feet.

559
00:42:03,486 --> 00:42:04,578
Thank you.

560
00:42:04,654 --> 00:42:05,746
Who's next?

561
00:42:07,323 --> 00:42:09,757
You know, l think I'm beginning

562
00:42:09,825 --> 00:42:11,258
to like this game.

563
00:42:11,327 --> 00:42:14,763
Just wait until he lands on
my old Kentucky home.

564
00:42:14,830 --> 00:42:16,263
More beer?
More beer.

